#: ../../api/runtime.md:13
msgid "`axiom.chronicler`"
msgstr ""

#: axiom.chronicler:1 of
msgid "core/chronicler.py"
msgstr ""

#: axiom.chronicler:3 of
msgid "The Chronicler Engine — Axiom AI's macro-simulation agent."
msgstr "Le moteur Chronicler — l'agent de macro-simulation d'Axiom AI."

#: axiom.chronicler:5 of
msgid ""
"The Chronicler simulates the independent evolution of the off-screen "
"world (factions, VIP NPCs, cities) without the player's involvement.  It "
"runs periodically (every N player turns, or on explicit time-skip events)"
" and produces JSON tool calls that update entity stats in the database."
msgstr ""
"Le Chronicler simule l'évolution indépendante du monde hors-champ "
"(factions, PNJ importants, villes) sans implication du joueur.  Il tourne"
" périodiquement (tous les N tours, ou sur saut temporel explicite) et "
"produit des tool calls JSON qui mettent à jour les stats d'entités dans "
"la base."

#: axiom.chronicler:11 of
msgid "Design principles"
msgstr "Principes de conception"

#: axiom.chronicler:12 of
msgid ""
"The Chronicler NEVER raises on malformed LLM responses.  A broken world "
"simulation is always preferable to a crashed game session."
msgstr ""
"Le Chronicler ne lève JAMAIS sur une réponse LLM malformée.  Une "
"simulation du monde cassée est toujours préférable à une session de jeu "
"plantée."

#: axiom.chronicler:14 of
msgid ""
"All updates are written to Event_Log with event_type='chronicler_update' "
"so they are included in checkpoint replays and can be rewound."
msgstr ""
"Toutes les mises à jour sont écrites dans Event_Log avec "
"event_type='chronicler_update', donc incluses dans les replays de "
"checkpoint et rembobinables."

#: axiom.chronicler:16 of
msgid ""
"World_Tension_Level (stored in Universe_Meta) throttles the severity of "
"simulated events: low tension → mundane shifts, high tension → "
"cataclysms."
msgstr ""
"World_Tension_Level (stocké dans Universe_Meta) module la sévérité des "
"événements simulés : tension basse → évolutions banales, tension haute → "
"cataclysmes."

#: axiom.chronicler.ChroniclerResult:1 of
msgid "The complete output of one Chronicler world-simulation run."
msgstr "La sortie complète d'un passage de simulation du monde du Chronicler."

#: axiom.chronicler.ChroniclerResult:5 of
msgid "entity_ids whose stats were changed."
msgstr "entity_ids dont les stats ont changé."

#: axiom.chronicler.ChroniclerResult:7 axiom.chronicler.ChroniclerResult:25 of
msgid "list[str]"
msgstr ""

#: axiom.chronicler.ChroniclerResult:11 of
msgid "Count of new Event_Log entries written."
msgstr "Nombre de nouvelles entrées Event_Log écrites."

#: axiom.chronicler.ChroniclerResult:13 of
msgid "int"
msgstr ""

#: axiom.chronicler.ChroniclerResult:17 of
msgid "The World_Tension_Level active during this run."
msgstr "Le World_Tension_Level actif pendant ce passage."

#: axiom.chronicler.ChroniclerResult:19 of
msgid "float"
msgstr ""

#: axiom.chronicler.ChroniclerResult:23 of
msgid "A list of major off-screen event descriptions."
msgstr "Une liste de descriptions des événements hors-champ majeurs."

#: axiom.chronicler.ChroniclerEngine:1 of
msgid "Simulates the off-screen world by calling the LLM periodically."
msgstr "Simule le monde hors-champ en appelant le LLM périodiquement."

#: axiom.chronicler.ChroniclerEngine:3 of
msgid "The LLM backend used for world simulation calls."
msgstr "Le backend LLM utilisé pour les appels de simulation du monde."

#: axiom.chronicler.ChroniclerEngine:4 of
msgid "Handles Event_Log writes and State_Cache reads."
msgstr "Gère les écritures Event_Log et les lectures State_Cache."

#: axiom.chronicler.ChroniclerEngine:5 of
msgid "Path to the universe .db for entity and meta queries."
msgstr "Chemin du `.db` univers pour les requêtes d'entités et de méta."

#: axiom.chronicler.ChroniclerEngine:6 of
msgid ""
"In-game minutes between automatic Chronicler runs. Defaults to 720 (12 "
"in-game hours)."
msgstr ""
"Minutes in-game entre deux passages automatiques du Chronicler. Par "
"défaut 720 (12 heures in-game)."

#: axiom.chronicler.ChroniclerEngine.should_trigger:1 of
msgid "Return True if the in-game clock crossed a trigger_interval boundary."
msgstr ""
"Retourne True si l'horloge in-game a franchi une frontière de "
"trigger_interval."

#: axiom.chronicler.ChroniclerEngine.should_trigger:3 of
msgid ""
"The Chronicler is driven by in-game minutes, not player turns: it fires "
"once whenever the world clock moves from one `trigger_interval`-minute "
"block into a later one. This makes a single long time-skip trigger "
"exactly one off-screen simulation, while many short turns accumulate "
"until they cross the next boundary (Pilier 5 / TICKET-018)."
msgstr ""
"Le Chronicler est piloté par les minutes in-game, pas par les tours "
"joueur : il se déclenche chaque fois que l'horloge du monde passe d'un "
"bloc de `trigger_interval` minutes à un bloc ultérieur. Un unique long "
"saut temporel déclenche ainsi exactement une simulation hors-champ, "
"tandis que beaucoup de petits tours s'accumulent jusqu'à franchir la "
"frontière suivante (Pilier 5 / TICKET-018)."

#: axiom.chronicler.ChroniclerEngine.should_trigger:9 of
msgid "Pure function — no I/O."
msgstr "Fonction pure — aucune E/S."

#: axiom.chronicler.ChroniclerEngine.should_trigger:11 of
msgid "The world clock (in-game minutes) after this turn."
msgstr "L'horloge du monde (minutes in-game) après ce tour."

#: axiom.chronicler.ChroniclerEngine.should_trigger:12 of
msgid "The world clock before this turn's time advance."
msgstr "L'horloge du monde avant l'avancée de temps de ce tour."

#: axiom.chronicler.ChroniclerEngine.should_trigger:14 of
msgid ""
"True when `previous_time` and `current_time` fall in different "
"`trigger_interval`-minute blocks (i.e. a boundary was crossed)."
msgstr ""
"True quand `previous_time` et `current_time` tombent dans des blocs de "
"`trigger_interval` minutes différents (une frontière a été franchie)."

#: axiom.chronicler.ChroniclerEngine.run:1 of
msgid "Execute one Chronicler world-simulation cycle."
msgstr "Exécute un cycle de simulation du monde du Chronicler."

#: axiom.chronicler.ChroniclerEngine.run:3 of
msgid "Steps:"
msgstr "Étapes :"

#: axiom.chronicler.ChroniclerEngine.run:4 of
msgid "Read World_Tension_Level from Universe_Meta."
msgstr "Lire World_Tension_Level depuis Universe_Meta."

#: axiom.chronicler.ChroniclerEngine.run:5 of
msgid "Fetch all active off-screen entities and their current stats."
msgstr "Récupérer toutes les entités hors-champ actives et leurs stats courantes."

#: axiom.chronicler.ChroniclerEngine.run:6 of
msgid "Build the Chronicler prompt."
msgstr "Construire le prompt du Chronicler."

#: axiom.chronicler.ChroniclerEngine.run:7 of
msgid "Call the LLM (non-streaming; expects only a JSON tool call)."
msgstr "Appeler le LLM (sans streaming ; n'attend qu'un tool call JSON)."

#: axiom.chronicler.ChroniclerEngine.run:8 of
msgid "Parse the resulting state_changes."
msgstr "Parser les state_changes résultants."

#: axiom.chronicler.ChroniclerEngine.run:9 of
msgid "Validate each change (entity must exist and be active)."
msgstr "Valider chaque changement (l'entité doit exister et être active)."

#: axiom.chronicler.ChroniclerEngine.run:10 of
msgid "Persist valid changes via EventSourcer."
msgstr "Persister les changements valides via l'EventSourcer."

#: axiom.chronicler.ChroniclerEngine.run:11 of
msgid "Return ChroniclerResult."
msgstr "Retourner un ChroniclerResult."

#: axiom.chronicler.ChroniclerEngine.run:13 of
msgid ""
"On any malformed LLM response the method logs a warning internally and "
"returns an empty ChroniclerResult — it never raises."
msgstr ""
"Sur toute réponse LLM malformée, la méthode journalise un warning en "
"interne et retourne un ChroniclerResult vide — elle ne lève jamais."

#: axiom.chronicler.ChroniclerEngine.run:16 of
msgid "The save that owns the entities being simulated."
msgstr "La save propriétaire des entités simulées."

#: axiom.chronicler.ChroniclerEngine.run:17 of
msgid "The current turn number (used for Event_Log turn_id)."
msgstr "Le numéro de tour courant (utilisé pour le turn_id d'Event_Log)."

#: axiom.chronicler.ChroniclerEngine.run:21 of
msgid "ChroniclerResult summarising what changed."
msgstr "ChroniclerResult résumant ce qui a changé."

#: axiom.chronicler.ChroniclerEngine.force_trigger:1 of
msgid "Explicitly trigger a Chronicler run regardless of turn threshold."
msgstr ""
"Déclenche explicitement un passage du Chronicler, quel que soit le seuil "
"de tours."

#: axiom.chronicler.ChroniclerEngine.force_trigger:3 of
msgid ""
"Intended for time-skip actions (sleeping, fast travel) where the player "
"has explicitly advanced time.  Semantically equivalent to run() but named"
" distinctly for call-site clarity."
msgstr ""
"Destiné aux actions de saut temporel (sommeil, voyage rapide) où le "
"joueur a explicitement avancé le temps.  Sémantiquement équivalent à "
"run(), mais nommé distinctement pour la clarté des sites d'appel."

#: axiom.chronicler.ChroniclerEngine.force_trigger:7 of
msgid "The active save."
msgstr "La save active."

#: axiom.chronicler.ChroniclerEngine.force_trigger:8 of
msgid "The current turn number."
msgstr "Le numéro de tour courant."

#: axiom.chronicler.ChroniclerEngine.force_trigger:10 of
msgid "ChroniclerResult from the simulation run."
msgstr "ChroniclerResult du passage de simulation."

